text:
What's there to say about Mitch and this company? He's a stand up guy. Whenever something happened at a rental property, or my personal property in Orange County, he would make the drive no problem and wouldn't complain! He'd make the drive and give me an honest opinion of what needs to be fixed or done! When he said he'd be there, he was there!

Mitch even helped my parents. My parents needed an entire unit replaced and he gave them the best price and beat others by thousands! Overall he's a very nice guy, and honest/straight up.  Whenever he came to Cerritos, Yorba Linda, Irvine, or Castaic, he really listened, and was very thorough. Whether it ended up being a big job or small job, he let me know what truly the issue was! He's a person I would definitely do business with again and again!

text: Honestly not worth the time and money you pay. I don't want to offend others who gave 5 stars and I think they have their reasons. I literally waited 1 hour for the food and another 30 min just to get the check. I understand that there are lots of customers but waiting this long really not worth the time. The food taste okay but the price is too high for the quality especially the New York strip ($60). It was the special menu and the waiter claimed to be A7 Wagyu. It does taste like that they claimed. There are only 5 dishes on the main and with professional kitchen, it should not take more than 30 mins. I would give 5 stars for the taste but combine with service and wait time 3 stars would be it. You can find tastier food with the same price. Personally the risotto was not up to the standard.

text:
On a trip to SB we decided to eat dinner at Shalhoob before heading home. Shalhoob is not located on the main street where lots of restaurants, bars and wineries are located.  I checked them on Yelp first was pleased that they had 4.5 stars.  

There is lot of free parking available.  Santa  Barbara has changed a lot, a lot of business here now charge for parking.  

We ordered the street corn which came in a pan, garlic fries, chicken wings, smoked chicken, ribs & mac N cheese; lot of food for 2 people...enough to feed four, buttered bread!!!  :-) The food is so tasty, they give very large portions as well.  They offer plenty outside seating with shade.  They cater events.  Some of the tables are barrels with umbrellas.  The service was GREAT.

I highly recommend this place, you won't be disappointed.
label: positive

text:
Jogged from Shoreline Park to Blenders for a smoothie, wasn't disappointed. 12oz = $4.35, 24oz = $5.85. I got the 12oz peanut butter banana smoothie (+ carob, dates, chia seeds, non-dairy soy blend (for +0.75)). It's really great how they allow for a free supplement - I chose chia seeds. I also was able to customize by adding in dates. The smoothie was creamy and perfect, filled to the top lid. Quick and efficient, no complaints!

This location also has ample parking and is close by Shoreline, nice for enjoying your smoothie with a view of the beach!

text: Very bad on-call services over the weekend. I had to call this office to get a hold of our pediatrician six times over the weekend. It took the on-call nurse 3 1/2 hours to call me back by the time she returned my car had gone to bed. It's very important to me as a mother and a registered nurse to be able to get in touch with my Pediatrician on the weekend if my child is sick but not ER urgent, at least not yet. It's very disheartening and disconcerting that there are no physicians who are able to be reached and that the nurses who are on call do not return your calls for hours. It's also challenging when you have to call the on-call number multiple times to even get a callback. My husband and I will be switching pediatricians after this experience because it's very important to me to be able to get in touch with a pediatrician over the weekend for urgent matters. I would not recommend this office or clinic if it is important to you to be able to have communication for urgent needs on weekends or evenings as they are unavailable. We did not feel supported nor cared for by this Clinic or Pediatrician from this experience.

text:
This is the absolute BEST Denny's in the entire state! I celebrated my Birthday yesterday and wanted to enjoy my annual and very traditional FREE Grand Slam as anticipated! 

Once at the restaurant, I experienced some technical issues with my online registration process, etc. Fortunately, Jenny and the other female associate working with her were able to assist me and process my birthday gift accordingly and satisfactorily. Both extended superb customer service , and truly made my own B-day special. 

This restaurant has proven time and again to offer the best food and service of any Denny's we have ever visited. We are becoming more frequent guests as a result, and have never experienced anything short of phenomenal service and delectable fare. 

Thank you again for exceeding every expectation on each and every visit. You are all superstars and deserve every accolade, recognition, and reward such comments tend to elicit. We will see you again soon, until then - stay safe and know you are all appreciated more than you could ever imagine.

text:
Wow this place has turned into a real dump. I don't remember the last time I came here because the last time the girl forgot to put turkey in my turkey sandwich but it was probably a little over a year ago. I was trying to decide what to order and got talked into a tri-tip torta. I asked how fresh the tri-tip was because I really hate when you get a "special" and it's 4 days old. I was assured it was fresh from that morning almost with too much assurance from everyone behind the counter. I also ordered a Chile Relleno heated up from the cold case. I couldn't decide which one I wanted and I figured I could save some for later. We wondered the store and grabbed some drinks and when we went to pick up the sandwiches they forgot about my Chile Relleno. I didn't have time to wait so I told them to forget it. Strike one. The tri-tip was disgustingly old but I was starving since it was 2:30 pm and my first time eating that day so begrudgingly ate pretty stinky meat. Strike two. I went back to work I started to feel queasy and hoped no one could smell the gross burps it was bringing up for the next 4 hours. STRIKE THREE. 

Ugh this place is awful! I used to love Cantwell's but I will definitely never go back and will actively tell anyone who will listen to not go there either. It used to be so busy but looking back on it there wasn't really anyone in there and it makes so much sense. STAY AWAY!
label: negative

text: Don't bother with this place.  I brought my phone in for a cracked screen, and the guy took 2 hours and literally THREE separate tries (after trying to hand it off to me as fixed 2x) to get the new screen working.  I decided to purchase a screen protector from them, and regret it.  The screen protectors are pricey and ineffective; mine cracked the entire screen under the protector after a 1ft fall off of the couch.  Big surprise, iGeek takes no responsibility for the failure of the screen protector nor offer a replacement.  Felt like a rip-off to be honest.  Definitely find somewhere else to take your broken electronics if you want effective products at literally the same price.
label: negative

text:
I received flowers on 1/4/21 from my children for the holiday and was disappointed with their quality.  Some of the flowers had brown edges and the chrysanthemums looked spent (meaning they weren't going to last much longer).  I am attaching images of the flowers that I took on the day that I received them. 

This has been niggling me for a week now, so I finally decided to let the Goodland Florist know about the impression that they made. Unfortunately, their online contact information would not work (and I am unable to communicate verbally if I feel like I am confronting someone about something). The captcha kept saying that there was an error, but would never refresh so that I could try it with a different code. I basically told them in the message the same thing that I am saying in this review.

I don't really expect anything to come of this. I was not the one who paid for the flowers but I know that good money was put out for these flowers and I was truly disappointed in them and the company that thought providing these flowers in this condition was acceptable. I do not want my children to know that there was a problem, so do not want a refund.  

I just want other consumers to know of this issue before they purchase flowers from Goodland Florist. I know that I always research a company before making purchases.
label: negative

text:
This place has the yummiest burgers EVER.  You definitely don't miss meat.  The ingredients are top quality and the food is seasoned to perfection.  My favorites are the Kale Burger, Sweet Potato Fries and ALL the Falafels.   The different textures and the flavors of the Kale burger are so amazing, the brioche bun is so soft and the burger is a good size so you will be full and you won't be able to stop thinking about it....it's that good.  

I don't care if you aren't into vegetarian food.....you will love this.

text: Pre-COVID I celebrated a birthday with a friend turning 99 and her daughter, their choice to eat at Jane. I ordered the tuna and shrimp salad but without the shrimp and hot water as a beverage, the daughter ordered the same salad with the shrimp. Her salad came with 3 shrimp and 3 pieces of tuna. I received the salad with 3 pieces of tuna!  Lovely company and pleasant eating outside. When the bill came I was horrified that I'd been charged for hot water!  A service charge of .75c! I didn't mention either the salad nor the hot water at the time because of the celebration, which was my bad. Never went back until Sunday 9/31 for dinner and asked if there was still a charge for hot water, and there is!  The planked salmon was good.
label: positive

text:
Just the name will make you smile. 

Then they have brioche. OMG brioche. 

Grab a loaf of it to go and have it every day with brie and jam. Or as a sandwich. Or just by itself. There is literally no wrong way to eat brioche, and you will want to do nothing but eat brioche once you've had theirs.

They make breakfast sandwiches and they are amazing. An Eggs & Salmon Brioche is just perfect, and a simple Eggs & Cheese Brioche is fully of goopy gruyere.

Grab a Sourdough Baguette if they have one but don't bother to get a bag because you'll eat the entire thing right away. We also tried both types of Cinnamon Roll and can't decide which is better. 

That's all I could justifiably try in a single trip, but I'm not above swinging back to Santa Barbara just for more of this because every mile would be worth my while.
label: positive

text:
The very first time I went here was my first year of college at UCSB. I remember that time being super delicious and flavorful. However, every time I go there now, I am very disappointed by the lack of flavor in the chicken and vegetables. 

It is a great price though, especially for the portion sizes! You have to get the creamy Sriracha mayo and teriyaki sauce on the side! That is what gives the food the flavor, plus it's just super tasty.  

I personally recommend getting the mini size. The container looks small, but trust me it's more than enough! The only difference between the mini and the small is that the small has more meat!

text: My husband and I came to Bacar to celebrate our honeymoon! We wanted to have some fine dining so we chose Angel Oak! Let me start off by saying that the outside seating has such a great and chill ambience. It's definitely a place to get dressed up for! The server brought us some prosecco to start off our celebration, which was very sweet. We ordered the spicy tuna on crispy rice, French onion soup, Caesar salad, and NY Steak! Everything was on point and delish! The Caesar salad was made with anchovies in the dressing and even tho I don't like the taste of anchovies, the salad was light and refreshing! The creme brûlée dessert was the best I've ever had! Highly recommend! The one negative thing I have to add is that the water tasted like dirt. Another table complained about the same thing! If that's a ruse for us to order bottled water, it worked.
label: positive

text:
We are VERY against Starbucks, and appreciate the smaller, local coffee shops that take the time and care about quality espresso.  There are only a few coffee houses that we frequent in Santa Barbara, and Handlebar is one of them!  Even when our European cousins come to town, we are literally there daily, on multiple occasions, for their espresso fix. 

We frequent the De La Vina location most, as we live in Goleta, and enjoy the larger outdoor patio that is pet-friendly.  

We also appreciate the Vegan menu item offered, Avocado Toast, that can be served with or without an egg on top. Make sure to ask for some salsa!

text:
Hard to get a hold of a plumber in SB.  I got lucky.  I ended up with Rooter Solution because they answered the phone and set up an appointment immediately.  My tech was Miguel Campos and he was polite, professional and efficient.  He knew his stuff and explained everything along the way and fixed my drain issue.

I liked that he made completely sure that there were no issues under the cabinet before he wrapped things up.

The best part was that Miguel was ultra tidy and probably left the area cleaner than when he found it.  Our issue was upstairs he was careful to make sure he covered his shoes and even wore his mask through the whole repair.

This was done just today so I'll update if there is any issues with the repair but it looks good so far.

Techs like that make me want to use Rooter Solutions again.  I highly recommend Miguel Campos and Rooter Solutions for your drain problems.
label: positive

Lomito suizo (#11 pork and gooey melted cheese between 2 handmade tortillas, looking almost like a pupusa) is the best thing of all the good things I tried (tacos, pork & vegetable tamale, enchilada). We'd never heard of it elsewhere, but after trying it on a whim on a previous visit, my brother-in-law craved it so much that he ordered 5. It looks taco sized but is maybe a tad more filling. 

Cash only. Very easy on the wallet.

text:
My girls and I were looking for some ice cream after our lunch date. A quick Yelp search later led us to McConnell's. There was a line of people waiting to place their order. I think we waited ago 15 minutes. Was it worth it? YUP. 

We all got the same flavor: earl grey tea with shortbread cookies. I added sea salt caramel to mine. The ice cream was BOMB. I would highly recommend it to all my fellow tea lovers! I would, however, skip on the caramel. It coagulated after melting my ice cream :(  
The caramel itself was good, though. 

Too bad there aren't any locations in NorCal! Otherwise, I'd frequent this place pretty often.

text: Where to even begin!? Shawna came highly recommended to me by many friends who work in the wedding business - and they were right to recommend her. From the very start, she was engaged, responsive,  organized and had a great energy/outlook. We met several times and had phone calls when we were not able to meet in person. She helped me bring to life the wedding that my husband and I envisioned. Not only is she detail oriented, but she can piece together seamlessly all the moving parts of the rehearsal and day of.  She dealt with our large bridal party (8 on each of our sides) and our crazy families with poise and grace. Not one time did I have to worry about what was happening or if anything was going wrong, because Shawna had it all handled. From start to finish, Shawna and her team ROCKED. She and her team were there before anyone else and were the last to leave. I couldn't imagine how our day would have turned out without them! 1000% would recommend.
label: positive
